<F P=100> Southeast Asia &amp; Pacific </F>
<H3> <TI>   Henan Secretary Seeks Singapore Investment </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0302055794 Zhengzhou Henan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0302055794 </F>
<F P=104>  Zhengzhou Henan People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] At the Stanford Hotel on the afternoon of 27 
January, the Singapore Chinese General Chamber of Commerce 
sponsored a meeting on Henan Province's foreign economic 
cooperation and investment environment. Henan provincial party 
Secretary Li Changchun briefed the participants on the 
province's investment environment and expressed a warm welcome 
to Singapore industrialists and businessmen's cooperating with 
Henan. [passage omitted] 
  Li Changchun's written speech was distributed to the 
participants. Li Changchun also explained to them Henan's five 
favorable conditions for the introduction of foreign investment. 
  First, Henan is located in the central plains and has 
convenient railway and highway transportation facilities and 
three civilian airports: Zhengzhou Airport, Luoyang Airport, 
and Nanyang Airport. Zhengzhou International Airport is still 
under construction and will be completed in 1996. 
  Second, it has a variety of mineral resources. Its outputs 
of farm products, industrial crops, and animal husbandry rank in 
the forefront of the country. It has adequate electric power 
supply. 
  Third, it has a long history and beautiful mountains and 
rivers and is rich in cultural relic resources. 
  Fourth, it is rich in labor resources and has low labor 
costs 
and hard-working and honest people. 
  Fifth, the two high-tech development zones in Zhengzhou and 
Luoyang, which have been approved by the State Council, provide 
good environments for foreign investors in Henan. The State 
Council has also provided Zhengzhou City with the preferential 
policies offered to Chinese open coastal areas. In addition, we 
have the same language for communication with each other, 
similar cultures, and the same habits and customs. This is also 
a favorable condition. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

