<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deng Yingchao's Birthday Commemorated in Beijing </TI></H3>
<H4>   Two Books Published </H4>
<F P=102> OW0202101794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0807 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0202101794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 2 (XINHUA) -- With the approval of 
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), two 
books on veteran proletarian revolutionary Deng Yingchao 
(1904-1992) have been published here in commemoration of the 
90th anniversary of her birth. 
  The two books -- "The Collected Works of Deng Yingchao" and 
"In Memory of Sister Deng" -- were compiled by the Party 
Literature Research Center of the CPC Central Committee and 
published by the People's Publishing House. 
  The 300,000-word "Collected Works of Deng Yingchao" contains 
89 articles, letters, reports and records of talks she gave in 
the period 1938-1992. 
  Deng took part in the May 4th movement of 1919 (an 
anti-imperialist, anti-feudal, political and cultural movement 
influenced by the Russian October revolution of 1917). She also 
served as chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese 
People's Political Consultative Conference. "In Memory of 
Sister Deng" has 72 articles written by her colleagues, friends, 
relatives and people working around her. Chinese party and state 
leaders Jiang Zemin and Li Peng, as well as Chen Yun, Bo Yibo 
and Chen Muhua wrote inscriptions for the book. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

