<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ismail Amat Views Progress in Minorities Work </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0202110994 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0647 
GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0202110994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By RENMIN RIBAO reporter Pan Yue (3382 6460) and XINHUA </F>
reporter Jia Fenyong (6328 1164 0516)] 
  [Text] Beijing, 27 Jan (XINHUA) -- A national work 
conference of nationalities affairs commissions was held in 
Beijing today. The conference will relay and study the 
guidelines of relevant central directives on improving 
nationalities work in the new period, review the achievements 
and experiences gained in recent years in this work, and study 
and arrange this year's nationalities work. 
  Wang Guangying, Cheng Siyuan, Buhe, and Wang Zhaoguo 
attended 
today's plenary session. Ismail Amat, state councillor and 
concurrently minister in charge of the State Nationalities 
Affairs Commission, delivered a report. He said: In recent 
years, China has made continuous progress and scored great 
success in nationalities work during the course of reform and 
opening up. After the central nationalities work conference in 
1992, various minority areas greatly expedited economic 
construction, reform, and opening up, thereby making speedy 
progress in economic construction. Township and town enterprises 
in minority areas developed greatly with the assistance of 
nationalities affairs departments at all levels. Poverty relief 
efforts in those areas yielded notable results, releasing 
approximately 250,000 people from poverty in two years. 
Minority areas made tremendous headway in various social 
services on the basis of economic development. The new type of 
socialist relationship among various nationalities was further 
consolidated and developed. People of all nationalities showed 
an even deeper love of their united and multinational 
motherland, and they worked even more conscientiously toward 
rejuvenating the Chinese nation. Meanwhile, enormous progress 
was made in instituting a legal system governing nationalities, 
resulting in the enactment and implementation of many laws and 
regulations in this regard. Relations among various 
nationalities and work regarding nationalities are being 
gradually written into laws. 
  Ismail Amat said emphatically: People engaged in 
nationalities work should seriously study Volume 3 of the 
Selected Works of Deng Xiaoping, arm themselves with 
the theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics, 
seriously study new circumstances and problems encountered by 
minority nationalities and minority areas in the course of 
establishing a socialist market economic system, energetically 
promote economic development, reform, and opening up in minority 
areas, and constantly make new contributions to the unity and 
progress of various nationalities. 
  Conferees included chairpersons of nationalities affairs 
commissions of various provinces, autonomous regions, 
municipalities directly under the central government, and cities 
with independent decision-making power; leading comrades in 
charge of work regarding nationalities from some provinces and 
autonomous regions; and responsible comrades from relevant 
departments under central state organs. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

