<DOCNO> FBIS3-26104 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi023_k_94014" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-023 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  3 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Six Officials Accused of Improper Behavior </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0202130394 Hong Kong CHENG MING in Chinese No 196, 1 Feb 
94 p 19 </F>

<F P=103> HK0202130394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong CHENG MING </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Reference News" by Wang Hui (3769 1920): "Reports About </F>
Malpractice of Six High-Ranking Officials Made"] 
  [Text] According to the Central Discipline Inspection 
Commission, NPC vice chairmen Ni Zhifu, Chen Muhua, and Li 
Ximing were reported by people of their localities and 
departments. They and their families reportedly were involved 
in economic problems. There were accusations that their sources 
of income are subject to suspicion. 
  Metallurgical Industry Minister Liu Qi and Water Resources 
Minister Niu Maosheng were reported for leading a corrupt life 
and for improper relations with women. CPPCC Vice Chairman Yang 
Rudai was reported by the Discipline Inspection Commission of 
Sichuan for his family's possession of 50,000-yuan in original 
issue stocks. It is learned that the Central Discipline 
Inspection Commission has already confirmed the reports about 
the six high-ranking officials. 

</TEXT>

