<F P=100> Northwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Qinghai Banking Conference Sets Tasks for 1994 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0302095794 Xining Qinghai People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0302095794 </F>
<F P=104>  Xining Qinghai People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] A provincial banking work conference was 
convened in Xining yesterday. At yesterday's conference, 
provincial Vice Governor Liu Guanghe delivered a speech in which 
he stated: This year, the province's banking work should focus 
on raising construction funds through all channels. Last year, 
the province's bank deposits registered an 18.86 percent 
increase and loans an 28.27 percent increase, totaling more than 
3 billion yuan, while the province's insurance premiums income 
exceeded 110 million yuan. 
  Vice Governor Liu Guanghe noted: This year, the province's 
banking departments should make continued efforts to raise funds 
through all channels and should whole-heartedly support 
provincial wide economic construction. To this end, he said, 
first, the province's banking departments should carry out basic 
work in a down-to-earth manner, exert their utmost to increase 
bank deposits, and take basic work as an important criterion for 
appraising overall work performance. Second, they should make 
flexible use of funds, speed up free flow of funds, and achieve 
higher funds utilization efficiency. The principal leaders of 
various localities and professional departments should take 
personal charge of loan recovery work in the same way they do 
loan provision work. Third, the province's banking departments 
should work hard to explore and discover new capital 
coordination channels to absorb as much idle capital in the 
society as possible. Moreover, banking departments should make 
every possible endeavor to ensure smooth issuance of local 
construction and enterprise bonds, safeguard and rectify the 
banking order, and ban irrational capital outflow. Fourth, the 
province's banking departments should make active efforts to 
raise all sorts of funds, develop insurance undertakings, 
increase insurance premiums income, and increase credit and loan 
sources. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

