<F P=100> Military </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reports on Views of PLA Chief Zhang Wannian </TI></H3>
<H4>   Promotes Army Reform </H4>
<F P=102> OW0302124394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1226 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0302124394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 3 (XINHUA) -- Zhang Wannian, a 
senior leader of China's armed forces, has pledged to promote 
the construction and reforms of the People's Liberation Army 
(PLA) in the new year. 
  Speaking at a meeting here yesterday, Zhang, chief of the 
general staff of the PLA, said that 1994 is a year crucial to 
the success of China's reforms, opening up and economic 
construction. 
  "Present developments make it imperative for us to promote 
the PLA construction and reforms and comprehensively enhance PLA 
fighting capabilities in order to provide a powerful guarantee 
of safety for China's reforms, opening up and modernization 
drive," he told senior officers. 
  According to General Zhang, in the new year all PLA officers 
and soldiers must follow Deng Xiaoping's theory of building 
socialism with Chinese characteristics and his ideas on army 
construction during the current period. 
  Zhang, who is also a member of the Central Military 
Commission, said that it is imperative for PLA army officers and 
soldiers to take the study of Volume 3 of the "Selected Works of 
Deng Xiaoping" and the theory of building socialism with Chinese 
characteristics as a primary task. 
  The general also stressed the importance of improving 
political consciousness and military skills of officers and 
troops, and of stepping up the reinforcement of leading bodies 
at all levels. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

