<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-023 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  3 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economic, Trade Commission To Train Cadres </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0302102894 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0534 
GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0302102894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Li Anding (2621 1344 1353)] </F>
  [Text] Beijing, 2 Feb (XINHUA) -- The State Economic and 
Trade Commission will provide training for the nation's cadres 
working at enterprises and cadres involved in economic work on 
the basic knowledge of socialist market economy. The training 
will focus mainly on reform of the fiscal and taxation, finance, 
foreign trade, and investment systems and on establishing a 
modern enterprise system. Chen Qingtai, vice minister of the 
State Economic and Trade Commission, announced this in Beijing 
at the ongoing National Work Conference on Training Cadres at 
Enterprises. 
  Chen Qingtai said, as this year is a critical year for 
promoting the establishment of a socialist market economic 
system and as the reform is approaching the homestretch, there 
is a need to train a contingent of entrepreneurs who are adapted 
to the socialist market economy and to greatly raise their 
political and professional quality to enable them to contribute 
to the reform and development of the economy and enterprises. 
Main points of the current training program include: stepping 
up training of plant directors and managerial personnel to lay a 
good foundation for forming a contingent of socialist 
entrepreneurs and for raising industrial and economic levels; 
helping cadres involved in economic management to gain a better 
understanding of the socialist market economy and to bring about 
transformation of functions at government departments and to 
effect changes in enterprises' operation mechanisms; 
strengthening study of existing reform measures so that the 
broad mass of cadres involved in economic work and cadres 
working at enterprises will understand and support reform and 
promote the smooth progress of reform. 
  Chen Qingtai said the commission plans to basically complete 
training of major leading cadres at state-owned large and 
mid-sized enterprises: 20,000 by the end of February and 100,000 
by the end of May; the commission will strive to basically 
complete training of major leading cadres at the nation's 
enterprises by end October. 
  Chen Qingtai pointed out: It is necessary to step up 
enacting laws for training of cadres involved in economic work 
and cadres working at enterprises; with macroguidance, to 
gradually establish mechanisms for training whereby enterprises 
will voluntarily offer their own training programs; to conduct 
bold experiments; and to constantly promote the development of 
training work for cadres working at enterprises amid reform. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

