<H3> <TI>   Reports on Travels of Premier Li Peng </TI></H3>
<H4>   Reportedly Visits Zhuhai </H4>
<F P=102> HK0302145394 Hong Kong AFP in English 1144 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> HK0302145394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Macau, Feb 3 (AFP)--Former Chinese president Yang 
Shangkun is vacationing at a posh resort in Zhuhai, next door to 
Macao, Portugal's Lusa News Agency reported Thursday. It said 
it was able to confirm that Yang, 87, was staying at the 
Shijingshan (Rockview Mountain) resort, where reporters found "a 
strong Public Security Bureau presence." There were also 
unconfirmed reports that Premier Li Peng was also in Zhuhai, 
ahead of this weekend's inauguration of the Daya Bay nuclear 
power plant northeast of Hong Kong, Lusa said. 
  But Zhuhai Mayor Liang Guangda ducked questions from Macau 
reporters when asked to confirm if Li was in town. "As far as I 
know, Premier Li Peng has arrived in Guangdong, but it is 
unclear yet what actually his situation in Zhuhai is," Lusa 
quoted Liang as saying. 
  Li last visited Zhuhai one year ago for three days. 
  Earlier reports in Hong Kong newspapers, quoting Guangdong 
officials, have said paramount leader Deng Xiaoping will be in 
the economically thriving province for the Lunar New Year 
holidays, which begin February 10. 

</TEXT>

