<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Frontier Police Handle 827 Smuggling Cases in 1993 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0202103394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0920 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0202103394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 2 (XINHUA) -- China's frontier 
police handled 827 smuggling cases in the coastal regions and 
border areas in the past year. 
  These included 201 cases involving more than 1 millon yuan 
in 
value each. 
  According to sources at the Ministry of Public Security, the 
total value of all the smuggled goods reached .5 [as received] 
billion yuan. The smuggled goods included automobiles, 
electronic appliances and cigarettes. The smuggling ativities 
were most widespread in the coastal regions. The public 
security department took effective measures to enhance control 
of vessels at sea. 
  Last year 706 vessels engaged in smuggling were seized by 
the 
public security organizations in coastal regions and 273 vessels 
which had no numbers, no names and no registration documents 
were caught along the coastlines of Guandong, Fujian and 
Zhejiang Provinces. 

</TEXT>

