<F P=100> Science &amp; Technology </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Peng Addresses Academy of Sciences Conference </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0302014294 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1312 
GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0302014294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Reporter Yang Zhaobo (2254 0340 3134) and correspondent Wu </F>
Lebin (0702 2867 2430)] 
  [Excerpt] Beijing, 29 Dec (XINHUA) -- The 1994 Work 
Conference of the Chinese Academy of Sciences closed today. Li 
Peng, premier of the State Council, sent a congratulatory letter. 
  The congratulatory letter states: Basically speaking, we 
need 
to rely on scientific and technological progress to realize our 
country's socialist modernization. The broad mass of scientists 
and technical workers shoulder a glorious yet arduous historical 
mission. It is my earnest hope that the broad mass of 
scientists and technical workers will, following the close of 
the conference, further implement the guidelines set forth at 
the 14th CPC National Congress and at the Third Plenary Session 
of the 14th CPC Central Committee; deepen reform of the 
scientific and technical structure; constantly promote 
scientific and technical progress in line with the scientific 
and technological development trend in the world and in 
integrating with the reality in our country; and make even 
greater contributions to the sustained, rapid, and healthy 
development of our country's economy. 
  Li Peng also states the following in his letter: As the 
Spring Festival, the traditional festival of the Chinese people, 
is approaching, I would like to wish you in advance a happy new 
year. Through you, I would also like to wish a happy new year in 
advance to all comrades throughout the nation who work hard on 
the scientific and technological front. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

