<F P=100> Science &amp; Technology </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fiber Optic Communication System To Be Built </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0302101494 Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE in Chinese 0928 
GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0302101494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hangzhou, 31 Jan (ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE) -- Another 
national-class fiber optic cable communication system--the 
Hangzhou (Fuzhou)-Guiyang-Chengdu trunk line--will be built in 
Zhejiang. Construction of the project will start in January and 
trial operation is scheduled in August next year. By that time, 
the province will have an additional 33,000 inter-and 
intra-provincial communication lines. 
  It has been reported that the project will run through three 
major regions--eastern, central south, and southwest China--and 
is an important component of the key fiber optic cable network 
to be built by the state during the Eighth Five-Year Plan 
period. The project starts from Hangzhou and Fuzhou in the 
east, passes through Jinhua, Quzhou, Shangrao, and Yingtan to 
reach Nanchang, and through Nanping and Fuzhou to reach 
Nanchang. The two lines merge into one in Nanchang and proceed 
to the destination of Chengdu via Changsha, Guiyang, and 
Chongqing. The overall length of the communication system is 
4,354 km with a total of 107 stations set up along the lines. 
The length within the boundary of Zhejiang Province will be 433 
km, and 10 stations will be set up in Hangzhou, Fuyang, Tonglu, 
Gantan, Jiande, Lanxi, Jinhua, Longyou, Quzhou, and Jiangshan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

