<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Article Reviews `93 Price Inspection Results </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0302100694 Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE in Chinese 1220 
GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0302100694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chengdu, 31 Jan (ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE) -- The 
national conference of price inspection office directors, 
concluded here the other day, reported that from January through 
November 1993, a total of 220,000 cases of price-related illegal 
practices and cases were handled nationwide. 
  According to the information, the illicit gain reaped 
through 
unlawful price increases discovered last year totaled 353 
million yuan, of which 87 million yuan was refunded. 
  The conference emphasized that the prices of people's daily 
necessities and charges for various kinds of services will 
become the main objects of inspection in the coming year. At 
present, inspection of the prices of grain, oil, meat, eggs, and 
vegetables should be well conducted and such irregularities as 
jacking up prices, seeking exorbitant profits, and disrupting 
market prices must be firmly handled. Unauthorized price 
increases and charges for railway, highway, and water 
transportation and forcing customers to buy insurance when 
selling or handling various kinds of tickets should also be 
dealt with according to law. 

</TEXT>

