<F P=100> TAIWAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   ARATS, SEF Official Meet on Ties in Beijing </TI></H3>
<H4>   Chiao: Ties To Be `Re-Sewn' </H4>
<F P=102> OW0302141794 Taipei CNA in English 1332 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0302141794 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Bear Li] </F>
  [Text] Beijing, Feb. 3 (CNA) -- Vice Chairman and 
Secretary-General Chiao Jen-ho of the Straits Exchange 
Foundation (SEF) Thursday [3 February] likened relations between 
Taiwan and Mainland China to a piece of clothing that has been 
cut and needs to be re-sewn. 
  Chiao made the remarks while meeting with Wang Zhaoguo, 
director of Beijing State Council's Taiwan Affairs Office, at 
the Great Hall of the People. 
  "We have to sew the cloth together slowly and patiently so 
as 
to make it flawless," Chiao said. 
  He said that mutual trust between the two sides could not be 
established overnight. 
  He said that people in Taiwan are paying great attention to 
his talks with Tang Shubei, his counterpart from the Association 
for Relations Across the Taiwan Strait (ARATS) because they see 
the meeting as a "touchstone" in the development of the 
cross-strait relations. 
  Wang said that Chiao's trip to Beijing is conducive to the 
further acceleration of Taiwan-Mainland ties. 
  He expressed the hope that a second round of talks between 
SEF Chairman Koo Chen-fu and ARATS President Wang Daohan would 
take place soon. The first, historic meeting was in Singapore 
in April. 
  Chiao's negotiations with Tang continue tomorrow after 
ending 
in a stalemate again Thursday. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

