<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jiangsu's Yangtze Port Expansion Attracts Investors </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0402074694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0714 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0402074694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Nanjing, February 4 (XINHUA) -- Expansion of the 
Lusi Port on the Chang Jiang River estuary has aroused great 
interest among foreign business people. 
  Located in east China's Jiangsu Province, which faces the 
newly-rising Pudong area zone in Shanghai, Lusi received 50 
groups of foreign investors last year. 
  After feasibility studies, Chinese and foreign experts 
agreed 
that the port is a natural link on the marine lines from Dalian 
in the northeast to Ningbo in the east and to Hong Kong in the 
south. 
  It is suitable for building at least 100 berths to 
accommodate ships of 10,000-dwt and 20 deepwater berths for 
100,000-dwt ships. 
  The port is listed in the national port planning and 
construction program, and will be developed into an 
international port soon. 

</TEXT>

