<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangzhou Cracks Down on `Seven Social Evils' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0402082094 Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE in English 0747 
GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0402082094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, February 4 (CNS)--According to relevant 
departments under the Guangzhou municipal government, the 
Guangzhou police and the cultural administrative department have 
in recent months severely cracked down on pornographic 
activities and the "seven social evils," catching a large number 
of law-breakers. 
  Between September and December last year, the city 
discovered 
more than 13,000 people involved in the "seven social evils," 
with more than 3,000 of them being prostitutes and their 
visitors and over 9,000 gamblers. At the same time, over 500 
criminal gangs were apprehended. 
  In addition, the city also cracked down on more than 1,000 
women working as hostesses, seized 59 kilograms of drugs, more 
than 4,000 copies of pornographic books and over 6,000 
pornographic video tapes. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-26261 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi024_p_94003" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-024 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  4 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Henan Governor Commends Armed Police Force </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0402024894 Zhengzhou Henan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0402024894 </F>
<F P=104>  Zhengzhou Henan People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An enlarged meeting of the party committee of the 
Henan armed police force headquarters closed yesterday, having 
lasted for four days. 
  During the meeting, Henan Governor Ma Zhongchen delivered an 
important speech on the province's reform and development, as 
well as the armed police force's role in the new period. In his 
speech Ma Zhongchen expressed his appreciation for the efforts 
and contributions made by the members of the armed police force 
in the past year to the province's economic construction. 
Having briefed the participants on the province's overall plan 
for economic development for the current year, Ma said: This 
year will see Henan Province undergoing the most intensive 
reform. In the wake of the introduction of some reformatory 
measures and the adjustment of interest relations, it is certain 
that some new circumstances and new problems will be emerging, 
and some unstable factors will be coming to the surface as well. 
When performing its duties, the armed police force is to do 
away with these unstable factors before they gain ground. In 
doing so the armed police force is supporting reform and 
development. Amid the great tide of reform, the armed police 
force will be playing still more important a role. Therefore 
you are expected to conscientiously sum up experience, work 
harder, strive for greater progress, and make greater 
contributions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

