<H3> <TI>   Hubei Stresses Importance of Social Stability </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0302105094 Wuhan Hubei People's Radio Network in Mandarin 
1000 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0302105094 </F>
<F P=104>  Wuhan Hubei People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] A provincial judicial work meeting ended today. 
During discussions with leaders of prefectural and city party 
committees on the evening of 28 January, Liu Rongli, secretary 
of the provincial commission for political science and law, 
stressed: We should firmly carry out the instructions of the 
party Central Committee and the provincial party committee on 
legal work, make comprehensive arrangements in light of local 
conditions, bring focal points into prominence, and be strict in 
work to ensure political stability and social tranquility 
throughout the province and to promote the smooth carrying out 
of reform, opening up, and economic construction. 
  Liu Rongli continued: A task of primary importance at 
present is to preserve social stability in a down-to-earth 
manner, to put into effect all policies and measures, and to 
strike severe blows at serious criminal offenses. [passage 
omitted] Leaders should pay close attention to wherever public 
security is chaotic, including highways and railways, should 
concentrate their efforts on rectifying social order in these 
places, and should not stop this rectification until social 
order changes for the better. 
  Liu Rongli stressed the need to strengthen party leadership 
over judicial work and to speed up improvement of the judicial 
contingent. The key to fulfilling the heavy tasks in judicial 
work is to build a good judicial contingent, to improve the 
political and professional quality of judicial cadres, and to 
raise their law enforcement ability. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

