<H3> <TI>   Tibet Highway Reaches Last Highwayless County </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0402075394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0732 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0402075394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lhasa, February 4 (XINHUA) -- A highway has been 
built to reach Medog, the last county in accessible by road in 
the Nyingchi region of the Tibet Autonomous Region. 
  The 141-km highway took about ten years and ten million yuan 
(1.15 U.S. dollars) [figure as received] to build because of the 
difficult terrain and conditions. It starts from Zhamu and ends 
at Medog. 
  A spokesman for the provincial communications department 
said 
that frequent collapses of snow and mountains as well as 
landslides caused the road-builders "unimaginable difficulties 
and sacrifices." 

</TEXT>

