<F P=100> Southwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yunnan Lists Eight Tasks for First Quarter </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0302141094 Kunming Yunnan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1000 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0302141094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kunming Yunnan People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Yesterday afternoon, the provincial government 
held a meeting for people in charge of commissions, offices, 
departments, and bureaus. Governor He Zhiqiang relayed the 
instructions of the provincial government's seventh executive 
meeting and arranged work for the first quarter of this year. 
  He Zhiqiang said: On the morning of 31 January, the 
provincial government held the seventh executive meeting to 
discuss work for the first quarter of this year. The basic 
principle for the work in 1994, under the guidance of Deng 
Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese 
characteristics and the party's basic line, is to 
comprehensively implement the instructions of the 14th CPC 
National Congress and the Third Plenary Session of the 14th CPC 
Central Committee, speed up the establishment of the socialist 
market economic structure, maintain sustained, speedy, and 
healthy development of the national economy, preserve political 
stability, and promote overall social progress. According to 
this basic principle, in the first quarter of this year, we 
should focus on eight tasks. 
  First, we should seriously sum up our work in 1993, fully 
confirm our achievements, find out shortcomings, and proceed 
with our work in 1994 enthusiastically with a scientific 
attitude. 
  Second, we should continue to combat corruption in 
government 
institutions. Yunnan has made certain achievements in combating 
corruption. [passage omitted] 
  Third, we should serious resolve new situations and new 
problems since the introduction of reform measures. The 
provincial government has formed 14 special groups on housing 
and price system reform, the salary of retired personnel, and 
other issues, to discuss the relevant problems and resolve them 
as soon as possible. 
  Fourth, we should do a good job in the construction of 
irrigation projects and in late autumn crop management to reap a 
good harvest. 
  Fifth, we should ensure market supplies and maintain price 
stability. 
  Sixth, we should pay close attention to arranging the lives 
and production of the people in disaster-stricken areas. 
  Seventh, we should make a success of industrial production 
and communications development, bring about a comprehensive 
balance in funding, power supply, and transportation, and ensure 
power supplies for the people during the Spring Festival. 
  Eighth, to usher in the upcoming second session of the 
eighth 
provincial people's congress and the second session of the 
seventh provincial committee of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference, we should make all necessary 
arrangements. 
  Zhang Baoshan, member of the provincial party committee's 
Standing Committee, as well as Vice Governors Niu Shaoyao and 
Wang Bingsheng attended the meeting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

