<F P=100> Northeast Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Liaoning Court Sentences 42 Criminals </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0402055694 Shenyang Liaoning People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1000 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0402055694 </F>
<F P=104>  Shenyang Liaoning People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Jinzhou city intermediate people's court 
respectively held public trial meetings in Jinzhou city, Yixian 
County, Beizhen, Heishan, and (Linhai) city on the morning of 3 
February. Seventeen criminals, including (Tong Xiangli) and (Wu 
Chunli), were sentenced to death and deprived of their political 
rights for life. After the meetings, these criminals who are 
guilty of the most heinous crimes were escorted to the execution 
grounds and executed by shooting. Another 25 criminals were 
sentenced to death with a stay of execution, life imprisonment, 
or to set terms of imprisonment. 
  A major gang of hooligans with (Tong Xiangli) and (Wu 
Chunli) 
as prime culprits ran wild for 12 years in Yixian, (Linhai), 
Jinzhou, and Pancheng areas. They killed persons with weapons, 
harmed the innocent, engaged themselves in looting, sought 
hegemony, and raped women. Individually, or in a group, they 
committed 211 cases of crimes and brought damages to over 200 
cadres and people. 

</TEXT>

