<F P=100> Northeast Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Liaoning Port Bonded Warehouse Opens for Business </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0402121394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1130 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0402121394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shenyang, February 4 (XINHUA) -- A bonded warehouse 
at Jinzhou port in Liaoning Province opened for business at the 
end of January. 
  The first of its kind in the western part of Liaoning 
Province, the 3,200 square meter warehouse is about 100 meters 
from the wharf. 
  An official in charge of the construction said that a second 
phase of the warehouse project is expected to be jointly 
constructed with foreign counterparts. 
  He said that in the second phase, a 3,000-square-meter 
closed 
warehouse and a bonded yard taking up about 750,000 square 
meters will be built. 
  Jinzhou port opened to shipping in October 1990. It now has 
three berths with annual handling capacity of 1.88 million tons. 
  By the end of 1995, the port will have six berths including 
two for oil transportation, and the annual handling capacity 
will reach 5 million tons. 

</TEXT>

