<F P=102>  HK0302134094 Xian Shaanxi People's Radio Network in Mandarin 
0010 GMT 30 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0302134094 </F>
<F P=104>  Xian Shaanxi People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] A provincial meeting of public security 
departmental and bureau chiefs closed in Xian a few days ago. 
Ai Pishan, chief of the provincial public security department 
attended and addressed the meeting. He stressed: As the Spring 
Festival is approaching, public security institutions at all 
levels should devote much attention to cracking criminal 
offenses and improving social order to ensure that the people 
will spend the Spring Festival peacefully and harmoniously. 
  He pointed out: Last year Shaanxi made gratifying 
achievements in cracking down on crime. But serious crimes will 
still remain prominent for a period of time to come. Public 
security institutions at all levels in the province should 
continue to persist in the policy of severely cracking down and 
striking relentless blows at all criminal offenses. Particular 
attention should be paid to cities and towns where major crimes 
frequently occur, and to factories, mines, and economic 
development zones along railways and highways where the 
situation in social order is complicated. Great importance 
should be attached to severe crackdowns on crime in Xian and 
Baoji. [passage omitted] 

