<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Refurbished Fujian Airport Reopens to Flights </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0402120894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1146 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0402120894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Fuzhou, February 4 (XINHUA) -- The airport of 
Wuyishan city, a tourist resort in east China's Fujian Province, 
re-opened to traffic on Thursday [3 February] after major 
expansion. 
  It already has two regular air routes: from Wuyishan city to 
Xiamen city, Fujian Province, and Wuyishan to Shanghai. Next 
month a regular service to Hong Kong is expected to start. 
  Located in the Wuyi Mountains in the northern part of 
Fujian, 
Wuyishan city has a national nature reserve and is a tourist 
area. 
  More than 6.22 million tourists went there between 1986 and 
1992. 
  The local government raised 100 million yuan to expand the 
Wuyishan Airport. The work started in 1992, and in November last 
year, new runways, parking areas, waiting rooms and office 
buildings were completed, while imported telecommunications and 
navigation facilities were installed. 

</TEXT>

