<H3> <TI>   Gansu Secretary Views People's Congress Work </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0302130894 Lanzhou Gansu People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0302130894 </F>
<F P=104>  Lanzhou Gansu People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Provincial party committee Secretary Yan Haiwang 
yesterday went to see comrades who had attended the seventh 
Standing Committee meeting of the Eighth Gansu Provincial 
People's Congress, which concluded in Lanzhou yesterday morning, 
including both the provincial people's congress standing 
committee members and those who attended the meeting as guests. 
  Secretary Yan Haiwang made a speech in which he emphatically 
called on people's congresses at all levels across the province 
to seize each and every excellent opportunity to deepen reform, 
expand opening up, promote development, maintain stability, and 
successfully further all types of work. 
  Yan Haiwang stated: Since the First Plenary Session of the 
Eighth Gansu Provincial People's Congress, people's congresses 
and deputies have successfully armed themselves with the theory 
of building socialism with Chinese characteristics, 
conscientiously implemented the spirit of the 14th CPC National 
Congress and the spirit of the Third Plenary Session of the 14th 
CPC Central Committee, and accomplished a lot in respect of 
stepping up provincewide socialist democracy and legal system 
building, material and spiritual civilization building, reform, 
opening up, and economic construction. 
  Yan Haiwang expressed the hope that people's congresses 
across the province will continually and closely concentrate on 
improving services for reform, opening up, and economic 
construction, bring into full play each and every power and 
function belonging to people's congresses as provided in the 
constitution, formulate laws and regulations at a faster pace, 
and improve supervision of both work and major decisions of the 
provincial people's government, higher people's court, and 
people's procuratorate. 
  Yan Haiwang also urged people's congress at all levels 
across 
the province to improve work and strengthen supervision in 
accordance with the law. In the end, Yan Haiwang called on 
party committees at all levels across the province to attach 
great importance to and strengthen leadership over the people's 
congress work, support people's congresses in exercising powers 
in accordance with the law, and give full play to people's 
congresses' role as legislative organs. 

</TEXT>

